<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1941-08-06T02:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1941-08-06T02:00:00-05:00" n="367" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d367">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/13673½:
                            Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Winant</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1941-08-06T03:00:00-04:00">August 6,
                                    1941—3 a.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2984. Personal for the Ambassador. Following is the President’s reply to
                            your No. 3428, August 5, 10 p.m.: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>“Think highly inadvisable make any statement at this time. In my
                                    judgement all that need be said is that Prime Minister is on
                                    short vacation. References to accompanying officers especially
                                    bad. Any statement <pb facs="0357" n="345" xml:id="pg_345"/> now
                                    is direct invitation to Germans to attack him and his party
                                    going and returning. When in doubt say nothing. Roosevelt.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>